Name: FOREST
Definition: Percentage of area covered by forest

Name: RR
Definition: Maximum elevation minus minimun elevation

Name: PRECIP
Definition: Basin average mean annual precipitation for 1981 to 2010 from PRISM

Name: SLOP30_30M
Description: Percent of basin with slope greater than 30 degrees?

Name: MINELEV
Definition: Minimum basin elevation

Name: DRNAREA
Definition: Area that contributes flow to a point on a stream (total drainage area minus non-contributing areas within basin)

Name: CANOPY_PCT
Definition: Percentage of drainage area covered by canopy comprised of classes 41-43 from 2001 National Land Cover Dataset

Name: SOILPERM
Definition: Average Soil Permeability

Name: JANMAXT2K
Definition: Mean Maximum January Temperature from 2K resolution PRISM 1961-1990 data. NOTE: Data Must be converted to Fahrenheit manually before entering.

Name: I24H2Y
Definition: Maximum 24-hour precipitation that occurs on average once in 2 years - Equivalent to precitation intensity index. https://hdsc.nws.noaa.gov/pub/hdsc/data/

Name: LC11Forest
Definition: Percentage of forest from NLCD 2011 classes 41-43

Name: ELEV1K
Definition: Mean basin elevation in thousands of feet

Name: FORESTP1
Definition: Percentage of area covered by forest + 1%

Name: A7500
Definition: Percentage of the drainage area above 7,500ft elevation

Name: JANMINT2K
Definition: Mean Minimum January Temperature from 2K resolution PRISM 1961-1990 data. NOTE: Data Must be converted to Fahrenheit manually before entering.

Name: SOILCAPACITY
Definition: Average Soil Capacity (From NRCS) https://www.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=e66bffd8e4614cc9bf3c770fe6a4d4fc

Name: MINANTEMP
Definition: Mean annual minimum air temperature in degrees Fahrenheit (PRISM)

Name: DRAINDENS
Definition: Basin drainage density; defined as total (perennial?) stream length divided by drainage area, in kilometers per square kilomete

Name: I6H100Y
Definition: Maximum 6-hour precipitation that occurs on average once in 100 years

Name: CSL1085LFP
Definition: Change in elevation divided by length between points 10 and 85 percent of distance along the longest flow path to the basin divide

Name: SOM
Definition: Percentage of organic matter in soils from SSURGO

Name: RUGGED
Definition: Ruggedness number computed as stream density (length of streams/HUC area) times basin relief

Name: COMPRAT
Definition: Measure of basin shape related to basin perimeter and drainage area

Name: SLOP50_30MP1
Description: Percent of basin with slopes greater than 50 degrees from 30M DEM + 1
Definition: Percent slopes greater than 50 degrees +1% calculated from a 30m DEM

Name: AREA
Definition: HUC area

Name: ELEV5K
Definition: %HUC above 5000 feet elevation

Name: ELEV6K
Definition: %HUC above 6000 feet elevation

Name: STATSCLAY
Definition: STATSGO Percentage of Clay Soils

Name: OUTLETELEV
Definition: Elevation of basin outlet (NWIS)

Name: BSLDEM30ff
Description: Mean Basin Slope from 30m DEM ft/ft
